d":"Mull, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kenneth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Scottish origin: Anglicized form of two different Gaelic names, <i>Cinaed</i> and <i>Cainnech</i>. The former was the Gaelic name of Kenneth mac Alpin (  d. 858 ), first king of the united Picts and Scots. The latter survives today in Scotland as the common Gaelic name Coinneach . Since early in the 20th century <i>Kenneth</i> has been in regular use and enjoyed great popularity as a given name well beyond the borders of Scotland."],"variants":[{"name":"Kennith","meanings":["Of Scottish origin: Anglicized form of two different Gaelic names, <i>Cinaed</i> and <i>Cainnech</i>. The former was the Gaelic name of Kenneth mac Alpin (  d. 858 ), first king of the united Picts and Scots. The latter survives today in Scotland as the common Gaelic name Coinneach . Since early in the 20th century <i>Kenneth</i> has been in regular use and enjoyed great popularity as a given name well beyond the borders of Scotland."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Kenneth MacKenneth of Kintail was born in 1150, in Mull, Argyll, Scotland as the son of Gilleoin Og MacKenneth. He married Lady Morna MacDougall about 1185, in Argyll, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1230, in Argyll, Scotland, at the age of 80, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1150–1230":"1150–1230","1165–1230":"1165–1230","1200–1278":"1200–1278","1120–1200":"1120–1200","1278":"1278","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1230":"1230","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","about 1185":"umbes 1185","Cromartyshire, Scotland":"Cromartyshire, Scotland","Mull, Argyll, Scotland":"Mull, Argyll, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","Kintail, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Kintail, Ross-shire, Sco